Technically you're supposed to be a customer but if you were at the co-op, realized the bathrooms are gendered (despite it being a relatively new building?!) and so walked down the street to Brewbakers to feel safe they'd be totally cool about it.

name: 555 E Cheves St, Florence, SC 29506, USA
Cafe Paradiso
directions: To your left as you walk in, there is one female stall, one male stall, and lastly an "Other" stall. Granted, the intention of this stall's existence seems to be more for humour than for safety, but it serves its purpose nonetheless.

name: AMC Sugarloaf Mills
directions: Inside of the movie theatre, so you have to pay to get in. Bathroom is labeled as "family restroom."
comment: You have to be inside the theatre, so if you want to see a movie in a place with a safe restroom, this is the place.

name: House of Yes
directions: Directly across from the front door - gendered restrooms.

name: Wendy's
comment: This is where I work and it is a trans friendly environment. The bathrooms are also single stall. I'm not sure what qualifies as being wheelchair accessible so I'm very sorry if this is mislabeled. There's no threshold to get over, the door is fairly wide and there are support rails next to the toilets.

name: Cafe Deux Soleils
comment: Entrance and manoeuvrability impaired by traditional door width.

directions: Family restroom all over the park

name: Y'opa frozen yogurt

name: Dirksen/Hart Office Building
directions:
Across from Dirksen 157 on first floor.

Corridor is a little hard to find; if you're in the in the middle of Hart by Mountains and Clouds sculpture, walk towards Dirksen through the middle corridor, and after Capitol Building displays there's a corridor on your right.  Bathrooms on the left.
comment: Totally public but you will have to go through security to get into the building (food/drink fine, suitcases fine, packages, knives, weapons not fine).  Male and female single-person bathrooms.

name: Hoppin' Grapes
comment: There's a sign saying "If you use the rest room without making a purchase, please tip the staff for keeping it clean" (or words to the effect).

name: Bellevue College
directions: There are some by the book shop and to the left of the cafeteria, outside the C building.
comment: Clean, private. If you're stealth and just don't feel comfortable around others of your born sex or the sex you want to transition to, I know cishets have used it--nobody will look at you funny or judge you going in or out.

name: 1720-1740 Pembina Hwy, Winnipeg, MB R3T, Canada
directions: In the pizza pizza on the east side of the street, in a hallway to the right of the cash registers.
comment: They've never made me buy anything to use these washrooms.

name: Booster juice
comment: You have to be a "paying customer" technically but the employees are cool if you just ask to use the washroom

name: Busboys and Poets, ,
